item.title: Cruise doctor questioned in NSW inquiry
item.description: The doctor on board the Ruby Princess told authorities there was no risk of coronavirus infection on the ill-fated cruise ship when it arrived in Sydney, an inquiry has heard.

item.title: Virus cases rise in northeast Chinese city
item.description: A northeastern city of 10 million people grappling with what is now China's biggest coronavirus outbreak has further restricted inbound traffic to contain the spread of the highly contagious disease.

item.title: NSW virus toll hits 33, teachers slam plan
item.description: An emergency response team and federal support have been sent to a Sydney nursing home where three residents have died amid 42 cases of coronavirus.

item.title: Apollo, Oaktree, BGH circling Virgin Aust
item.description: Private equity and distressed situation specialists Apollo Global Management, Oaktree Capital Management and BGH Capital are among those that have expressed interest in restructuring Virgin Australia, five sources said.

item.title: UK PM under fire over crisis handling
item.description: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson is facing a call for an inquiry into his government's handling of the coronavirus crisis after failing to fully explain partial death data, limited testing or the lack of equipment for hospitals.

item.title: Refugee mounts coronavirus court challenge
item.description: A refugee in immigration detention is launching a court challenge against the Morrison government over its handling of the coronavirus.

item.title: Woman in custody over Gold Coast stabbing
item.description: A woman is in police custody after a man collapsed from a stab wound on a Gold Coast footpath and later died.

item.title: COVID-19 to crush Vic economy: Treasurer
item.description: As the coronavirus pandemic pushes Victoria towards a "catastrophic" economic downturn not seen since the 1990s, the state will lift its tight restrictions on elective surgery.

item.title: Economic reform, global action after virus
item.description: Scott Morrison is turning his mind to economic reform and overhauling global bodies as Australia's coronavirus infection rate plummets.

item.title: Zero Qld COVID cases, thousands lose job
item.description: Queensland has no new coronavirus cases for the second time this week but the impact of the pandemic has hit home with 130,000 people now out of a job or working reduced hours.
